</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ec7c8b114718">
<td data-local-id=3D"007f8d5d1ff7" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"58959dcb206e">706</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a5f615bc7fe4" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"94d71ced9767">BuyerInvoiceValidateContractUnitPriceRobot</p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"33bb200c9156" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0816e3429074">The robot evaluates the contract unit price ag=
ainst the unit price on imported invoices. If there is a mismatch, a warnin=
g or an error message will appear based on organization settings:<br>
=E2=80=A2 Warning - A warning message is displayed. The workflow step is co=
mpleted but details of the discrepancy are added into History.<br>
=E2=80=A2 Error - An error message is displayed. The invoice will stop on t=
he workflow step and details are added to the History. Users can adjust the=
 invoice, or they have the option to Restart, Skip or Reject on the workflo=
w step.</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5f91043ec1c5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0858dd73e197"></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"532958db863c">
<td data-local-id=3D"d988b7dc5759" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ff695844fb13">718</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"962ba3c12a52" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e90c82f4782f">BudgetManagerSpendCollectionBudgetCheckInvoice=
Robot</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"211008569508" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cda7e1524875">Budget Manager related robot. Collects spend, =
performs a budget check and flags document based on pass/fail status.</p></=
td>
<td data-local-id=3D"503c53776b6e" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2505bd2823cf"></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2517907a2b93">
<td data-local-id=3D"36c2de9b2b6c" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bcd156ddb9cf">721</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2dce5ce55780" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4ba88f52beb0">CreatePaymentRobot</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0b6252bb0835" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0e0ba9533ab2">This Robot allows the Payment document to be c=
reated automatically for the invoice that has registered supplier (i.e., no=
t a manual supplier), if the org setting <strong>"Enable JAGGAER Pay Automa=
tion Process</strong>" is true.</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"345436822094" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b323f60b9281"><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue3">The wo=
rkflow robot is setup as follows:</span></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">&lt;Wor=
kflowFolderMessage&gt;
  &lt;Folder name=3D"Create Payment" folderType=3D"automated"&gt;
    &lt;WorkflowType&gt;invoice&lt;/WorkflowType&gt;
    &lt;FolderRobot&gt;CreatePaymentRobot&lt;/FolderRobot&gt;
  &lt;/Folder&gt;
&lt;/WorkflowFolderMessage&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"da37c18db361">The activity configuration looks like this:</p=
>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">&lt;Act=
ivity name=3D"Auto Create Payment"&gt;
    &lt;ActivityType&gt;automated&lt;/ActivityType&gt;
    &lt;StepRef name=3D"Auto Create Payment" /&gt;
    &lt;FolderRef name=3D"Create Payment" /&gt;
    &lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[Document.IsAutoPaymentAllowed =3D=3D true]]&gt;=
/Rule&gt;
    &lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;ExplicitFolder&lt;/FolderSelectionRule&gt;
 &lt;/Activity&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d27ef9154025">
<td data-local-id=3D"cca974d20cce" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c3de8975df0e">727</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"adcec896b7c9" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"66d189245164">CreatePaymentCreditAllocationRobot</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"aea588c997ca" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"48ad103a56ff">Establishes Account Credit Buckets that will b=
e available for specific Payment Accounts to redeem on a JPay Payment.</p><=
/td>
